JavaInheritance.Inheritance in Java is when a child class inherits the properties of the parent class. There are certain types of inheritance in Java as mentioned below:


Single JavaInheritance.Inheritance
Multilevel JavaInheritance.Inheritance
Hierarchical JavaInheritance.Inheritance
Multiple JavaInheritance.Inheritance
Hybrid JavaInheritance.Inheritance


*The extends keyword indicates that you are making a new class that derives from an existing class. The meaning of "extends" is to increase the functionality.
*JavaInheritance.Inheritance represents the IS-A relationship which is also known as a parent-child relationship.


Multiple JavaInheritance.Inheritance is not supported in JAVA:
Diamond Problem:

Consider a scenario where A, B, and C are three classes. The C class inherits A and B classes. If A and B classes have the same method and you call it from child class object, there will be ambiguity to call the method of A or B class.

-> errors at compile time.